Cicero had written a long and exultant letter to Pompey, to which the latter had sent a very cold reply not now extant. To this reply oi Pompey we here have Cicero's answer. On the general form of the letter read Introductory Note on Roman correspondence (p. 333), referred to hereafter as R. C.
